\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Pre-flight endorsement rates across three item types ($n=10$ each) on the synthetic bait set. Type A (genuine universal rules) maintains high endorsement (mean$=0.95$) regardless of intervention; Type B (bait/confabulation items) shows endorsement$=0.00$; Type C (document-extensional facts) varies by axis. Kruskal-Wallis $H=27.36$, $p=1.14\times 10^{-6}$. These results confirm axis separability on synthetic items but cannot be generalized to real document hallucinations without a matched real-output calibration study.}}{6}{figure.2}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:preflight}{{2}{6}{Pre-flight endorsement rates across three item types ($n=10$ each) on the synthetic bait set. Type A (genuine universal rules) maintains high endorsement (mean$=0.95$) regardless of intervention; Type B (bait/confabulation items) shows endorsement$=0.00$; Type C (document-extensional facts) varies by axis. Kruskal-Wallis $H=27.36$, $p=1.14\times 10^{-6}$. These results confirm axis separability on synthetic items but cannot be generalized to real document hallucinations without a matched real-output calibration study}{figure.2}{}}
